Port Proton's steamclient trampoline system to upstream Wine 11.5.

When native steamclient.so is loaded inside Wine, its functions live at
addresses that Wine's PE loader doesn't know about. Calls into those
addresses trigger execute-fault SIGSEGV. This patch intercepts those
faults in the signal handler and redirects execution to lsteamclient.dll
equivalents. For 64-bit steamclient, we skip DllMain but allow import
fixup. For 32-bit, we skip import resolution entirely and re-read the
original ImageBase from disk. The tier0_s64/vstdlib_s64 imports are
redirected to ntdll.dll to satisfy steamclient64's dependencies.

Trampoline entries persist after DLL unload so the fault handler can
redirect cached function pointers even after steamclient64 is unmapped.
On reload at the same base, stale entries are purged before new ones
are added. Per-module tracking via steamclient_mods[] prevents cross-
module interference between steamclient64 and gameoverlayrenderer64.

The pinned module (LoadCount=-1) is protected from build_module's
post-import LoadCount=1 reset, ensuring FreeLibrary can never unmap it.

Ported from proton-wine-10.0-4 (Valve), with lifecycle fix.

